enttyp.enttypd: These sites represent all PIT Tag interrogation sites with PTAGIS records.

attr.attrdef: Internal feature number.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: A 3-digit character string code which uniquely identifies PTAGIS interrogation sites.
The short name of the interrogation site, as provided by the PTAGIS interrogation data contributors.
The type of PTAGIS interrogation site.

edom.edomvd: Detection equipment is placed to detect PIT-tagged fish passing through an adult fish ladder, or other passage structure intended for use by adult salmonids. May also incorporate detection equipment in adult fish traps. If the adult ladder leads to a hatchery, the site will be categorized as Hatchery Returns, instead.
Detection equipment is placed to detect PIT-tagged fish passing through both adult and juvenile passage structures.
Detection equipment is placed to detect PIT-tagged fish returning to a hatchery or associated facility.
Detection equipment is placed to detect PIT-tagged fish caught by a juvenile fish trap, such as a screw trap.
Detection equipment is placed to detect PIT-tagged fish in small streams.
Detection equipment is placed to detect PIT-tagged fish passing through juvenile bypass structures.
Detection equipment is placed to detect PIT-tagged fish as they are released from a hatchery or associated facility.

Detection equipment is placed to detect PIT-tagged fish passing through a series of trawl nets that are being towed by boats. This is the only type of interrogation site where the location is not fixed.

edom.edomvds: Detection equipment is placed to detect PIT-tagged fish returning to a hatchery or associated facility.
Detection equipment is placed to detect PIT-tagged fish passing over a spillway at a dam.

attr.attrdef: Latitude (in NAD 83 decimal degrees) of the interrogation site, as calculated in ArcMap. For interrogation sites linked to the Fish Facility dataset (FacID IS NOT NULL), this value is based on the field 'FacLatitude'.

Longitude (in NAD 83 decimal degrees) of the interrogation site, as calculated in ArcMap. For interrogation sites linked to the Fish Facility dataset (FacID IS NOT NULL), this value is based on the field 'FacLongitude'.

attrdomv.udom: This text string contains a wide range of values and thus cannot be represented by a domain.

attr.attrdef: A field used to record the location of the interrogation site, in river kilometers. This is a hierarchical coding scheme denoting the distance of interrogation location and intermediate tributaries from the mouth of the Columbia River. For example, the RKM of 522.173 for Lower Granite Dam reflects a distance of 522 km from the mouth of the Columbia River to the mouth of the Snake River, and 173 km from the mouth of the Snake River to Lower Granite Dam. The distances in these coded values may not be accurate, and the entire value should be considered an address, rather than an accurate measure of distance.
The first year the interrogation site was in operation.
The last year the interrogation site was in operation. Note that active sites will list the current year in this field.

The unique and primary key for the Fish Facility dataset. There are value ranges for each type of facility (FacID min - max = Facility Type): 1 - 999 = Hatcheries, 20,000 - 29,999 = Dams, 30,000 - 39,999 = Fish Traps, 40,000 - 49,999 = Fish Passage Facilities, 50,000 - 59,999 = PTAGIS Instream Detection Sites. Note that although only one type of PTAGIS interrogation site type is listed in the Fish Facility dataset, other facility types are associated with PTAGIS interrogation sites.
The common or official name of the facility. Note that this value is only present where 'FacID' IS NOT NULL.

attrdomv.udom: The values in this field represent the official or common name of the facility and thus cannot be represented by a domain.

attr.attrdef: This is the Unique Identifier for the whole-stream assigned and managed by the StreamNet parntership. The ID is assigned based on the 'LLID' system where the first 7 digits of the stream mouth's longitude are concatenated with the first 6 digits of the stream mouth's latitude to create a 13 character string ID that uniquely identifies the stream. It is important to note the method of using coordinates to derive the ID is only intended to ensure the uniqueness of the original ID assignment. It is not intended to be a 'smart code' and does NOT change if the location of the stream mouth differs through time. See the LLIDSrc field to determine which agency assigned the LLID for a given stream. NOTE: StreamNet's Location Referencing System requires that the LocationID Identifier be unique across all watercourse, waterbody and point location features. It serves as the unique ID for georeferencing fish data across all topologies.

attrdomv.udom: This field is a 13 character text field which contains unique IDs for streams.

attr.attrdef: The measurement (in feet) from the mouth of the stream, as measured from StreamNet's Mixed Scale Hydrography (ver. 3.1). Note that most locations are simply associated with this stream and measurement, as they are not located directly on the hydrgraphy, but are associated with the stream for reporting and analysis purposes.

Name of the stream feature as assigned by the StreamNet partnership. In the case of 'unnamed streams' the stream's LocationID is associated with the unnamed feature in the name field. For labeling purposes, users may wish to exclude 'unnamed streams'.

attrdomv.udom: This field contains labels for stream and thus cannot be represented by a domain.

overview.eaover: This layer contains fields from the PTAGIS database as well as the Columbia Basin Fish Facility dataset. The fields 'Latitude', 'Longitude', 'FacID', 'FacName', 'FacLLID/LocationID", 'FacMeas', 'StreamName', and 'TribToName' come from the Columbia Basin Fish Facility dataset. The fields 'SiteCode', 'Name', 'Rkm', 'SiteType', 'OperationsOrganization', 'FirstYear', 'LastYear', 'HUC8Code', 'HUC8_Name' and 'SiteStaus' are maintained in PTAGIS and are joined prior to publishing. The remaining link fields are calculated from other fields and specific URL text strings.

dataExt.exDesc: This dataset contains all PTAGIS interrogation sites, both decommissioned and presently active, current as of the time indicated in the End Date/Time of the listed Temporal Period Extent.

dataIdInfo.idPurp: This dataset shows the locations of Columbia Basin PIT Tag Information System (PTAGIS) interrogation sites.
dataIdInfo.idAbs:
An interrogation site is a location, usually fixed, where automated equipment is installed that is capable of detecting passive integrated transponder (PIT) tags. Equipment consists of at least one or more antennas through which, or over which, fish tagged with PIT tags may pass, and ore or more transceivers which decode, and in some cases store, the PIT tag code and time of detection.

Visit www.ptagis.orgfor more information.

For some sites, such as Combined Dam Locations, one location represents more than one site, so the site is generally placed at the main dam location. Trawl Net sites are best-estimate point representations of an activity which is not fixed. If you locate any errors in this dataset, please contact PTAGIS: https://www.ptagis.org/support/contact-us

dataLineage.statement: Location data were provided to PTAGIS from a variety of sources over the history of the project. In order to facilitate data coordination and improve the locational accuracy of shared facility data amongst Pacific States Marine Fisheries Commission's (PSMFC) Columbia Basin fish data programs, an effort was made in late 2014 to update point locations and create a common fish facility dataset for use by these programs. The process of updating fish facility locations created a master point dataset from which the majority of these locations are derived. The field "FacID" represents the unique identifier of the Columbia Basin Fish Facilities dataset. The data were then joined with varoius attribute data from PTAGIS to create this dataset.

prcStep.stepDesc: A table of PTAGIS interrogation sites was provided to the PSMFC GIS Center in November 2014. This table contained X and Y values for listed locations of all PTAGIS interrogation sites. It also contained other attributes from PTAGIS such as 'IntSiteCode', 'IntSiteName', 'RKM', 'IntSiteType', 'OperationsOrganization', 'FirstYear', 'LastYear', and 'SiteStaus'.

stepSrc.srcDesc: The Columbia Basin Fish Facility dataset contains point locations of fish facilities where fish are managed, counted or passed, and generally where there is at least one record in a Pacific States Marine Fisheries Commission database.

prcStep.stepDesc: The table of PTAGIS interrogation sites and the original locations were cross-referenced with the developing Columbia Basin Fish Facility dataset, and a new field (PTAGIS_IntSiteCode) was added to that dataset in order to track which facilities contain PTAGIS interrogation sites. Once all PTAGIS interrogation sites were identified with a corresponding record in the Columbia Basin Fish Facilities dataset, that subset was saved to a new dataset (PTAGIS Interrogation Sites). This core dataset is then periodically joined and updated with PTAGIS data such as status and years of operation, in order to maintain currentness and to locate new PTAGIS interrogation sites to be added to the dataset.
